&lt;/h1&gt;</description></item><item><title>kill</title><link>https://kingye.me/note-cs/docs/basic/pl/shell/command/kill/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://kingye.me/note-cs/docs/basic/pl/shell/command/kill/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="kill"&gt;
 kill
 
 &lt;a class="anchor" href="#kill"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
 
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h3 id="kill--9-与-kill-的区别"&gt;
 kill -9 与 kill 的区别
 
 &lt;a class="anchor" href="#kill--9-%e4%b8%8e-kill-%e7%9a%84%e5%8c%ba%e5%88%ab"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
 
&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;kill 等于 kill -15，是安全的
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;TERM&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;kill -9 是不安全的
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;SIGKILL&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;kill&lt;/code&gt; aka &lt;code&gt;kill -TERM&lt;/code&gt; aka &lt;code&gt;kill -15&lt;/code&gt; is the safe and correct way of terminating a process.
It&amp;rsquo;s equivalent to safely shutting down a computer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;kill -9&lt;/code&gt; is the unsafe way of brutally murdering a process.
It&amp;rsquo;s equivalent to pulling the power cord, and may cause data corruption.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;参考：&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/43724467/what-is-the-difference-between-kill-and-kill-9"&gt;what-is-the-difference-between-kill-and-kill-9&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://askubuntu.com/questions/184071/what-is-the-purpose-of-the-9-option-in-the-kill-command"&gt;what-is-the-purpose-of-the-9-option-in-the-kill-command&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.cnblogs.com/yucongblog/p/6568374.html"&gt;Linux kill -9 和 kill -15 的区别&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>netcat</title><link>https://kingye.me/note-cs/docs/basic/pl/shell/command/netcat/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://kingye.me/note-cs/docs/basic/pl/shell/command/netcat/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="netcat"&gt;
